  "prompt": "Has California ever voted for a Republican in the general election?",
  "response": "Yes, California has voted for Republican candidates in several general elections, particularly during the mid-to-late 20th century. Here are some notable examples:\n\n1. **Dwight D. Eisenhower** (1952 and 1956) \u2013 California voted for the Republican candidate in both of his presidential campaigns.\n2. **Richard Nixon** (1960, 1968, and 1972) \u2013 Nixon, a native Californian, won the state in all three of his presidential runs (though he lost nationally in 1960).\n3. **Ronald Reagan** (1980 and 1984) \u2013 Reagan, a former governor of California, carried the state in both of his successful presidential bids.\n4. **George H.W. Bush** (1988) \u2013 Bush won California by a narrow margin in his first presidential campaign.\n\nSince 1992, however, California has consistently voted for Democratic presidential candidates, becoming a reliably blue state in national elections. The last time California voted for a Republican in a presidential election was in 1988 with George H.W. Bush.",
